ts of the biopsy and EBUS/mediastinoscopy.**\n\n\n**Limitations and Uncertainties:**\n\nThis staging is provisional and based solely on imaging findings.  Confirmation through tissue biopsy is essential for definitive diagnosis and subtyping of the lung cancer. The absence of prior imaging studies limits the assessment of disease progression. The clinical significance of the right supraclavicular lymphadenopathy needs to be confirmed with further investigation. The accuracy of staging depends on the completeness of the imaging evaluation and the absence of occult disease.\n\n**Patient-Centered Care Considerations:**\n\nThe patient's overall health status, comorbidities (diabetes, hypertension, osteoarthritis), performance status, and preferences will all play a significant role in treatment planning.  A multidisciplinary team approach is essential to ensure optimal management.  Open communication with the patient is crucial throughout the diagnostic and treatment process.",
